page.title: 01Liphook to Linchmere
page.content: Five sixth of the above numbered block is contained within the Aministrative Countyy of West Sussex and is extremmelyy rural and sparsely populated. By complete contrast the whole of square No 1 andd the north western halves of squares Nos 2 & 5 fall within Hampshire and embrace most of the urbanised village of Liphook Liphook has good road and rail links with London and is popular residential area with affluent city commuters. However,it does have an ordnance factory which directly abuts a light industrial estate accommodting a score of small companies. The terrain within the West Sussex portin of the block is hilly and largely tree covered,except for half a dozen smal farms which are presently changing over from livestock to arable husbandry.
